  Vnn(A) = Contribution of Atom A to Nuclear Repulsion Energy of Molecule
           Calculation of Vnn(A) assumes satisfaction of the atomic virial theorem:
                2T(A) + Ven(A) + Vee(A) + Vnn(A) - W(A) = 0
  VeeC(A) = Coulomb Part of Vee(A)
  VeeX(A) = Exchange-Correlation Part of Vee(A)
